  "zipball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/ProvableHQ/leo/zipball/leo-lang-v4.1.0",
  "body": "Leo 4.1.0 builds on the 4.0 language model with read-only **view functions**, a bytecode **peephole optimizer**, multi-package **workspaces**, a new **language server**, and a refreshed build/release pipeline. It targets snarkVM 4.7.1 (consensus V15).\n\n## View Functions (V15)\n\nPrograms can now expose read-only `view fn` entry points — functions that query on-chain state and return values **without producing a transaction**.\n\n```leo\nprogram token.aleo {\n    mapping balances: address => u64;\n\n    // Read-only: reads state, produces no transaction.\n    view fn get_balance(user: address) -> u64 {\n        return balances.get_or_use(user, 0u64);\n    }\n}\n```\n\nViews support primitive, composite (struct), and tuple outputs. Requires consensus V15 / snarkVM 4.7.x.\n\n## Workspaces\n\nMulti-package projects are now supported — workspace globs, `--workspace`, and auto-adding members — so libraries and programs can be built and managed together.\n\n## Optimizer & Codegen\n\n- New **peephole optimization pass** over generated Aleo bytecode.\n- Algebraic simplification rules in SSA constant propagation, plus expanded common-subexpression elimination.\n- A **Checks-Effects-Interactions (CEI) analysis pass**.\n- Multiple codegen correctness fixes (deterministic constructor labels, record-cast member ordering).\n\n## Language Server\n\nA new `leo-lsp` language server with **go-to-definition**, **find all references**, **semantic highlighting**, and richer diagnostics.\n\n## ABI & Interfaces\n\n- `leo abi` now handles imports; wasm-friendly ABI generation via the new `leo-aleo-abi-wasm` crate.\n- Dynamic interface access syntax and interface ABI inheritance.\n\n## Diagnostics\n\nError messages normalized to a consistent rustc-style voice with help text throughout, plus fixes to error-span rendering.\n\n## CLI & Devnet\n\n- New flat, per-compilation-unit **build directory layout**.\n- **Persistent storage** for the local devnode.\n- Access to external program submodules; frontend passes now run on library packages.\n\n## Stability\n\nNumerous type-checker, parser, and compiler fixes to prevent panics/ICEs on malformed or recursive input.\n\n## Compatibility\n\n- Rust **1.96.0**\n- snarkVM **4.7.1** / snarkOS **4.7.1** (consensus V15)\n\n**Full changelog:** https://github.com/ProvableHQ/leo/compare/v4.0.2...leo-lang-v4.1.0\n\n---\n\n## Compatible Versions\n\n| Component | Version | Downloads |\n|-----------|---------|-----------|\n| `leo-lang` | [4.1.0](https://github.com/ProvableHQ/leo/releases/tag/leo-lang-v4.1.0) | [release assets](https://github.com/ProvableHQ/leo/releases/tag/leo-lang-v4.1.0) |\n| `leo-fmt` | [4.1.0](https://github.com/ProvableHQ/leo/releases/tag/leo-fmt-v4.1.0) | [release assets](https://github.com/ProvableHQ/leo/releases/tag/leo-fmt-v4.1.0) |\n| `leo-lsp` | [4.1.0](https://github.com/ProvableHQ/leo/releases/tag/leo-lsp-v4.1.0) | [release assets](https://github.com/ProvableHQ/leo/releases/tag/leo-lsp-v4.1.0) |\n| `snarkvm` | [4.7.1](https://crates.io/crates/snarkvm/4.7.1) | [crate](https://crates.io/crates/snarkvm/4.7.1) |\n| `snarkOS` | [4.7.1](https://github.com/ProvableHQ/snarkOS/releases/tag/v4.7.1) | [release assets](https://github.com/ProvableHQ/snarkOS/releases/tag/v4.7.1) |\n"
